% Italian conversational content words observed in chat-sim transcripts.
% These are NOT function words — they are common Italian filler/noun/verb forms
% that the fallback word-reflecting path would otherwise catalogue as unknown.
% Adding them as stopwords is the honest move: the system DOES see them but
% cannot reason about them; claiming "I don't know about X" for every one
% is the catalogue-of-ignorance anti-pattern.
stopword(niente).
stopword(nessun).
stopword(tranquillo).
stopword(confusione).
